turns.speaker: M
turns.content: As a matter of fact, the real cause of that row was Peter Burden.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: There was nothing in that, you know that.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I knew nothing of the sort.  You took presents from him.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Presents a trivial little broach.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I remember it well bristling with diamonds in the worst possible taste.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Not at all.  It was very pretty.  I still have it and I wear it often.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You went out of your way to torture me over Peter Burden.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I did not.  You made the whole thing up in your jealous imagination.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You must admit that he was in love with you, wasn't he?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Just a little perhaps, nothing serious.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You let him kiss you.  You said you did.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: What of it?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What of it?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It gave him a lot of pleasure and it didn't hurt me.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What about me?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: If you hadn't been so nosey, you never would have known a thing about it.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: That's a nice point of view, I must say.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh, dear.  I'm bored with this conversation.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: So am I.  Bored stiff.  Want some brandy?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No thanks.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I'll have some myself, I think.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I don't see why you want it.  You've already had two glasses.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: No particular reason.  Anyway they were very small ones.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: seems so silly to go on and on and on with such a thing.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You can hardly call three liquor glasses in the whole evening going on and on and on.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It's become a habit with you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You needn't be so grand just because you don't happen to want any at the moment.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh, don't be so stupid.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Really, Amanda.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: What?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Nothing.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Going somewhere, my dear?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Just making myself fascinating for you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Ah, that reply has broken my heart.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: The woman's job is to allure the man.  Watch me a minute will you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: As a matter of fact, that's perfectly true.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh, no it isn't

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Yes, it is.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh, be quiet.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: It's a pity you don't have anymore brandy.  It might have made you a little less disagreeable.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It doesn't seem to have worked such wonders with you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Snap, snap, snap like a little adder.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Adders don't snap they sting.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Non-sense they have bags of venom behind their fangs and they snap.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: They sting.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: They snap.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I don't care, okay.  Do you understand?  I don't care.  I don't mind if they bark and roll about like hoops.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Did you see much of Peter Burden after our divorce?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Yes, I did quite a lot.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I suppose you let him kiss you a good deal more then.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Mind your own business.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You must have had a riotous time.  No restraint at all, very enjoyable, you never had much anyhow.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You're quite insufferable.  I expect it's because you're drunk.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I'm not in the least drunk.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You always had a weak head.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I think I mentioned once before that I had three minute liquor glasses of brandy the whole evening long.  A child of two couldn't get drunk on that.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: On, the contrary.  A child of two could get violently drunk on only one glass of brandy.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Very interesting and how about a child of six and a child of four and a child of nine.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh, shut up.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: They'd get up a splendid little debate about that, you know.  Intemperate tots.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Not very funny, dear.  You'd better have some more brandy.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Very good idea.  I will.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You'd better turn that off I think.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Why?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: It's very late and it will annoy the people upstairs.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: There is no one upstairs.  It's a photographer's studio.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: There are people downstairs I suppose.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: They're away in Tunis.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: This is no time of year for Tunis.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Turn it on again, please.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I'll do no such thing.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Very well if you insist on being boorish and idiotic.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Turn it off.  It's driving me mad.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You're far too temperamental.  Try to control yourself.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Turn it off.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Go away, go away.  I hate you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Amanda, listen.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Listen? Listen indeed.  I'm sick and tired of listening to you.  You damn sadistic bully.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Stop.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Very amusing.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Stop, stop.  I hate you.  Do you hear?  You're conceited and overbearing and utterly impossible.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You're a vile tempered, loose living, wicked little beast. And I hope I never see you again as long as I live.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: This is the end do you understand?  The end,

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You're not going like this.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: finally and forever

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh, I am.  Let go of me.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You're not.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh, I hate you. It's a good thing that I found out in time what you're really like. Marry you again?  Never, never, never.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Shut up.  Shut up. I wouldn't marry you again if you came crawling to me on your bended knees.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You're a mean, evil minded, little tempered witch. I hope to God I never set eyes on you again as long as I live. Whore.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I'd rather die in torment. Beast.  Brute.  Calf swine.
